## 3. Data

**Galaxies.** 166 SPARC galaxies; 80/20 stratified split by morphology; all rotation curves read from *_rotmod.dat; baryonic components combined in quadrature; RAR computed in SI units with inclination hygiene (30Â°â€“70Â°).

**Clusters.** CLASHâ€‘based catalog (Tier 1â€“2 quality). **N=6** used for calibration; **2 blind holdâ€‘outs** (A1689, MACS1149); complex mergers like MACS0717 tracked separately. We store {Î¸_E^obs, z_l, **P(z_s)** or z_s medians, M_200c, c_200c} and compute clusterâ€‘specific M_500, R_500 and Î£_crit. **Sourceâ€‘redshift distributions P(z_s)** are included where available; otherwise lognormal approximations. **BCG/ICL** stellar mass included (~10^{11â€“12} Mâ˜‰).

**Hierarchical inference.** Two models:  
1) **Baseline** (fixed â„“_0) with population A_c ~ N(Î¼_A, Ïƒ_A).  
2) **Massâ€‘scaled** with (â„“_{0,â‹†}, Î³) + same A_c population.  
Sampling via emcee; priors and bounds in Appendix.

