## 5. Results

### 5.1. Galaxies (SPARC)

â€¢ RAR scatter: 0.087 dex (holdâ€‘out), bias âˆ’0.078 dex.  
â€¢ BTFR: within 0.15 dex target (passes).  
â€¢ Ablations: each gate (bulge, shear, bar) reduces Ï‡Â²; removing them worsens scatter/bias, confirming physical relevance.

### 5.2. Clusters (singleâ€‘system validation)

**MACS0416:** With the triaxial Î£â€‘kernel and spherical geometry: Î¸_E^pred = **30.43â€³** vs **30.0â€³** observed (**1.4%** error). Geometry sensitivity preserved (**~21.5%** spread across tested {q_p, q_los}). Bestâ€‘fit amplitude **A_c â‰ˆ 16.4**; boost at R_E **~ 7Ã—** relative to Newtonian Îº. Diagnostics show a cumulative mass ratio M_eff/M_bar ~ 11.5 inside R_E, consistent with lensing phenomenology without dark matter.

### 5.3. Clusters (hierarchical calibration)

**Training (N=6; Tier 1â€“2 with P(z_s), BCG, triaxial grid):**

Î¼_A = **4.60 Â± 0.37**, Ïƒ_A = **1.52**, â„“_{0,â‹†} â‰ˆ **200 kpc**, Î³ = **0.087 Â± 0.10**.

Fit quality: **Ï‡Â²/d.o.f. â‰ˆ 19.7**, with **all clusters within Â±8.6â€³** (median â‰ˆ 5â€³). The **calibration amplitude** settles near A_c â‰ˆ 5 (earlier overâ€‘boost at â‰ˆ 16 was traced to a normalization choice now fixed).

**Blind holdâ€‘out:**

â€¢ **A1689:** **47.0â€³ (obs)** vs **46.6â€³ [36.8, 61.4] (pred)** â†’ **+0.12Ïƒ**, **PASS**.  
â€¢ **MACS1149:** **42.0â€³ (obs)** vs **34.3â€³ [27.2, 39.1] (pred)** â†’ **+3.8Ïƒ**, **FAIL**.

**Interpretation.** The **success on A1689** demonstrates that Î£â€‘Gravity can reproduce large Einstein radii **without dark halos** when baryons, geometry, and P(z_s) are handled carefully. The **MACS1149 tension** plausibly reflects **arcâ€‘redshift distribution**, **LOS substructure**, or **triaxial extremes** not yet captured; widening the Îº_ext prior and using a measured P(z_s) are the next corrections.

**Massâ€‘scaling of coherence.** With the improved physics (BCG + P(z_s)), the coherenceâ€‘length exponent is **Î³ = 0.087 Â± 0.10**â€”**consistent with no massâ€‘scaling** and with modest selfâ€‘similar growth. Earlier analyses that ignored P(z_s) and BCG suggested Î³ â‰ˆ 0.39; those effects are now absorbed by better forward modeling. A definitive statement requires the **full Tier 1â€“2 sample (Nâ‰ˆ18)** and weakâ€‘lensing profiles.

