## 6. Discussion

**Where Î£â€‘Gravity now stands.**  
â€¢ **Solar System:** kernel vanishes (Kâ†’00) by design; Cassini/PPN limits passed with margin â‰¥1Ã—10Â¹Â³. **No wideâ€‘binary anomaly** at detectable levels.  
â€¢ **Galaxies:** competitive or better than MOND on RAR (0.087 dex) without modifying GR; universal 7â€‘parameter kernel.  
â€¢ **Clusters:** realistic baryons + Î£â€‘kernel reproduce A1689 strong lensing (Â±0.12Ïƒ) with Î¼_Aâ‰ˆ4.6; population geometry and massâ€‘scaling (Î³) now falsifiable.

**Major open items and how we address them.**  
1) **Sample bias & redshift systematics** â†’ now modeling D_LS/D_S explicitly, clusterâ€‘specific M_500, triaxial posteriors, and measured P(z_s) where available; expanding to Nâ‰ˆ18 Tierâ€‘1+2 clusters.  
2) **Outliers & mergers** (e.g., MACS0717, MACS1149) â†’ treat disturbed systems as multiâ€‘component Î£ or apply temperature/entropy gates to decohere shocked ICM; test robustness with weakâ€‘lensing profiles and individual arc redshifts.  
3) **Physical origin of A_c, â„“_0, and Î³** â†’ pathâ€‘integral interpretation under development (stationaryâ€‘phase kernel in progress); Î³ is **falsifiable**: Î³â‰ˆ0 = fixed coherence length; Î³>0 = selfâ€‘similar growth with halo scale.  
4) **Model comparison** â†’ run Î³â€‘free vs Î³=0 with Î”BIC/WAIC (decision threshold |Î”BIC|â‰¥6); blind posteriorâ€‘predictive checks on holdâ€‘outs; compare to Î›CDM (NFW) fits on same data.

**Why it works.** Disk galaxies supply long, phaseâ€‘aligned path families (ring winding + coherence length); hot ICMs supply broad projected surface density where the Î£â€‘kernel peaks (100â€“300 kpc); triaxiality modulates the path density along the line of sight. The missing mass effect arises from **coherent superposition of nearâ€‘stationary gravitational paths** through extended baryonic structures, **not** from modifying GR or adding nonâ€‘baryonic particles. Solarâ€‘System safety is **builtâ€‘in**: saturation gates enforce Kâ†’00 at small scales; no conflict with perihelion precession, Shapiro delay, or Cassini tracking.

---

## 7. Predictions & falsifiability

â€¢ Triaxial lever arm: For fixed baryons, Î¸_E should change by â‰ˆ15â€“30% as q_LOS varies from ~0.8 to 1.3.  
â€¢ Mass scaling: If A_c increases with cluster mass, relaxed highâ€‘mass clusters should lie on a narrower Î¸_Eâ€“mass locus than disturbed systems.  
â€¢ Weak lensing: Î£â€‘Gravity predicts shallower Î³_t(R) declines at 100â€“300 kpc relative to pure Newton, testable with stacked samples.  
â€¢ No Solarâ€‘System anomaly / no wideâ€‘binary anomaly at detectable levels.

