## 11. Limitations & Open Issues

1. **Phenomenological coherence windows.** The current coherence functions (damping, length scales) are empirically calibrated rather than derived from first principles. A full pathâ€‘integral derivation is in progress; the stationaryâ€‘phase kernel suggests our working forms are the leadingâ€‘order approximation. **Action:** Complete stationaryâ€‘phase formalism and compare predictions to current empirical fits.

2. **Baryon field fidelity (clusters).** Predictions depend on f_gas normalization, clumping C(r), BCG/ICL stellar mass, and pressure profile shape. Systematic uncertainties can shift Î£ by factors of 2â€“5. **Mitigation:** Use standardized gNFW (Arnaud+2010) normalized to f_gas(Râ‚…â‚€â‚€)=0.11; apply literature clumping corrections consistently; include BCG+ICL stellar components. **Test:** Vary f_gas by Â±20% and clumping models to quantify sensitivity.

3. **Triaxial geometry uncertainties.** Current q_plane, q_LOS priors are weakly informed (Unif[0.6,1.4]); Xâ€‘ray isophotes provide constraints for some clusters but not all. Geometry contributes ~20â€“30% lever arm in Î¸_E. **Action:** Incorporate weakâ€‘lensing shear to constrain halo shapes; use multiâ€‘wavelength morphology (Xâ€‘ray + optical + lensing) for joint posteriors.

4. **Sourceâ€‘redshift distributions.** Some clusters lack measured arc redshifts or P(z_s); we use median z_eff or lognormal approximations. MACS1149 failure (âˆ’3.8Ïƒ) likely reflects missing or incorrect P(z_s). **Action:** Obtain spectroscopic arc redshifts for all calibration + holdâ€‘out clusters; model P(z_s) explicitly in likelihood.

5. **Massâ€‘scaling exponent Î³.** With N=6, Î³=0.087Â±0.10 is consistent with 0 (no massâ€‘scaling) but also consistent with modest selfâ€‘similar growth. **Decision criterion:** |Î”BIC|â‰¥6 between Î³=0 and Î³â€‘free models. **Action:** Expand to Nâ‰ˆ18 clusters + weakâ€‘lensing profiles to achieve Î”Î³âˆ¼0.05 precision.

6. **External convergence Îº_ext.** Currently Îº_ext ~ N(0,0.03Â²); larger LOS structures could contribute Îº_ext~0.05â€“0.10 (correlated across nearby sightlines). **Test:** Widen prior to N(0,0.05Â²); crossâ€‘check against weakâ€‘lensing maps and simulations.

7. **Mergers and substructure.** Disturbed systems (MACS0717, MACS1149) may require multiâ€‘component Î£ or entropy/temperature gates to decohere shocked gas. **Action:** Develop temperatureâ€‘dependent coherence gate; test on Bullet Cluster and other wellâ€‘studied mergers; compare offsets between stellar BCG and lensing centroids.

8. **Elliptical galaxies and pressure support.** Current kernel is optimized for rotationally supported disks; pressureâ€‘supported ellipticals may require modified coherence damping. **Scope:** Apply projected Î£â€‘kernel to SÃ©rsic/Hernquist models; test on local ellipticals with stellar kinematics.

9. **Cosmology and structure formation.** Î£â€‘Gravity is currently an **astrophysical effective theory** (static/quasiâ€‘static halos). Extension to cosmological linear perturbations, CMB, and BAO requires full relativistic treatment. **Roadmap:** Derive K(k) for shear 2â€‘point functions; pilot CMB lensing angular power spectrum.

10. **Reproducibility and provenance.** All runs must record: catalog MD5, prior choices, geometry grids, P(z_s) models, random seeds, sampler diagnostics (R_hat, n_eff). **Status:** Implemented for current N=6 runs; checklist in Section 11 (Reproducibility).

