### 12.6. Mergers & Bullet Cluster

**Challenge:** Bullet Cluster shows BCG/stellar centroid offset from lensing peak by ~150 kpc; classic "smoking gun" for collisionless DM.

**Î£â€‘Gravity hypothesis:** Shocked ICM gas loses coherence (entropy jump â†’ decoherence); lensing follows **unshocked gas + BCG**.

**Test:**
1. Map Bullet Xâ€‘ray temperature; identify shock front (T_X jump, Mach number).
2. Apply entropy/temperature gate: K_Î£ â†’ 0 where Î”S > threshold or T_X > T_shock.
3. Predict lensing centroid from coherent (unshocked) gas component + BCG stellar mass.
4. Compare to observed strongâ€‘lensing and weakâ€‘lensing mass maps.

**Falsifiability:** If lensing centroid coincides with shocked gas (not BCG/unshocked gas), Î£â€‘Gravity is falsified.

