## 13. Conclusion

Î£â€‘Gravity offers a single, conservative kernel that **preserves GR locally**, **matches the galactic RAR at 0.087 dex**, andâ€”when paired with realistic baryons (BCG, P(z_s)) and triaxial projectionâ€”**reproduces cluster strong lensing** with a population amplitude **Î¼_A â‰ˆ 4.6**. A **blind A1689** prediction succeeds (**0.12Ïƒ**); MACS1149 remains discrepant, pinpointing where clusterâ€‘specific arc redshifts and substructure must be incorporated. Current data show **Î³ = 0.087 Â± 0.10** (consistent with **no massâ€‘scaling**), but earlier analyses suggested Î³ â‰ˆ 0.39 before BCG/P(z_s) were includedâ€”a **falsifiable test** of selfâ€‘similar vs fixed coherence. Upcoming work extends the calibration to **Nâ‰ˆ18 CLASH clusters** with measured P(z_s), weakâ€‘lensing profiles, and additional blind holdâ€‘outs, providing a decisive comparison with **Î›CDM (NFW)** and **MOND**.

